==English==

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|acid|fy|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|acidus||sour, acid}}; compare French {{m|fr|acidifier}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-acidify.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acidif|ies}}

# to make something (more) [[acidic]] or [[sour]]; to convert into an [[acid]].
# to [[neutralize]] [[alkalis]], as to '''acidify''' sugar
# to sour, to [[embitter]].
#:* His thin existence all '''acidified''' into rage. - [[w:Thomas Carlyle|Thomas Carlyle]]

